-- Hot Jumps to Two-Year High as Cool Plans to Raise Stake in Cable TV Firm
-- B y   R o n i t   G o o d m a n
-- 2010-10-27T14:41:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-27/hot-jumps-to-two-year-high-as-cool-plans-to-raise-stake-in-cable-tv-firm.html
Hot Telecommunication System Ltd. 
jumped to the highest close in more than two years after Cool
Holding Ltd. agreed to raise its stake in the Israeli cable
television and telecommunications company to about 66 percent.  The shares jumped 7.2 percent to 49 shekels at the 4:30 p.m.
close in Tel Aviv, the highest level since May 2008.  Cool will buy a 13 percent stake of Hot from Yediot
Communications Ltd. and 6 percent from the Fishman Group, Hot
said today in a statement to the Tel Aviv Stock Exchange.  “The acquisition is a positive and necessary step for
Hot,” said  Gilad Alper , an analyst at Meitav Investment House
Ltd. in Tel Aviv. “Hot will finally have one owner with
excellent experience and reputation in the telecommunications
market that will revamp the company.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
